      {
        "uuid": "80c8bae12a3d48d9a101a4b08fb69d19",
        "template": "Speedtest Cloudflare by HTTP",
        "name": "Speedtest Cloudflare by HTTP",
        "description": "Internet performance monitoring against Cloudflare's edge (speed.cloudflare.com).\n\nUses native Zabbix HTTP agent + JavaScript preprocessing - no external scripts, binaries, or UserParameters required. The master item fetches /cdn-cgi/trace (tiny, gives PoP/country); the JS preprocessing then performs N timed latency probes plus one download and one upload via HttpRequest, returning a single merged JSON document consumed by the dependent items.\n\nMethodology notes (be honest about limitations):\n- Single-stream HTTP throughput. Comparable to Ookla / LibreSpeed only at the order-of-magnitude level. May underreport on very high-BDP links (>500 Mbps with high latency) where multi-stream tools win.\n- Measures speed against the closest Cloudflare PoP, not a generic 'internet' server. For ISP plan validation that is usually what you actually want.\n- No packet-loss measurement (HTTP cannot expose it cleanly).\n- Payload sizes default to 5 MB download / 2 MB upload to fit comfortably inside Zabbix server's JS preprocessing time budget. Increase via macros if your Zabbix server Timeout allows and your link is fast enough.",
        "groups": [
          {
            "name": "Templates"
          }
        ],
        "items": [
          {
            "uuid": "3c8ec7ec5aa046d780f1482d6c684d42",
